5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to local commissions and authorities; to
10 remove the prohibition against a municipal official serving on
11 a municipal planning commission for municipalities with less
12 than 7,500 residents; to remove the prohibition against a
13 municipal officer serving on a county water, sewer, or fire
14 protection authority; and to remove the prohibition against a
15 county or municipal officer serving on a solid waste disposal
16 district or authority if the officer does not serve on the
17 governing or appointing authority.
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
19 Section 1. Notwithstanding Section 11-52-3, Code of
20 Alabama 1975, municipalities with 7,500 residents or less may
21 authorize individuals who hold a municipal office to serve on
22 a municipal planning commission, pursuant to Chapter 52 of
23 Title 11, Code of Alabama 1975.
24 Section 2. (a) Notwithstanding Chapters 88 and 89 of
25 Title 11, Code of Alabama 1975, a county commission may
26 authorize municipal officers to serve on a board of directors
27 for a county water, sewer, or fire protection authority.
28 (b) This section shall not affect the prohibition on
Page 1

(b) This section shall not affect the prohibition on
HB468 Engrossed
29 state or county officers from serving on any county board of
30 directors for a water, sewer, or fire protection district or
31 authority pursuant to Chapters 88 and 89 of Title 11, Code of
32 Alabama 1975.
33 Section 3. Notwithstanding Chapters 89 and 89A of Title
34 11, Code of Alabama 1975, an appointing or governing authority
35 of a municipality or county may appoint any county or
36 municipal official who does not serve on the appointing or
37 governing authority to a solid waste disposal district or
38 authority.
39 Section 4. This act shall become effective on October
40 1, 2026.
